'''La MICA Biological Station''' was a biological field station near [[Parque Nacional General de División Omar Torrijos Herrera]] in [[El Copé]], [[Coclé Province]], Republic of [[Panama]]. La MICA was established in 2007 by Julie M. Ray, a Ph.D. student from [[Old Dominion University]] studying Panamanian snakes.<ref>[http://www.odu.edu/ao/news/media.php?todo=details&id=13454 ''ODU Doctoral Student Pursuing Her Dream in Panama'' article from January 5, 2009.]</ref>
