{{nihongo|'''Institute for Research in Humanities, Kyoto University'''|京都大学人文科学研究所|Kyōto Daigaku Jinbun Kagaku Kenkyūjo}} is an institution for research into the humanities and ethno-ecological studies. It has a distinctive school tradition, as heir to the philosophically-oriented [[Kyoto School]], but differs from the latter in its broader cultural interests.<ref>Much of this article will be translated from the equivalent article [[:ja:京都大学人文科学研究所]], in the Japanese Wikipedia, as retrieved on June 24, 2007.</ref>

