Written by [[Mark Wallington (Writer)|Mark Wallington]], '''''The Man Who Lost His Head''''' is a 2-hour, comedy drama starring [[Martin Clunes]], on the theme of [[cultural repatriation]]. It was a  joint production for [[TVNZ]] in New Zealand and [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] in the United Kingdom. It was first broadcast on Sunday 26 August 2007 at 9 pm on [[ITV1]] in Britain and 8:30 pm on [[TV One (New Zealand)|TV ONE]] in [[New Zealand]].

The show was filmed entirely on location in New Zealand. The action took place in the fictional town of Otakataka but was in fact mostly filmed on the West Coast of the [[North Island]], around [[Huia (place)|Huia]] and [[Bethells Beach]].


